The club day hosted at Polokwane Golf Club saw 77 golfing enthusiasts competing for a win on Saturday. Players competed in a betterball Stableford format over 18 holes. Nola and Weyden Peceur finished first overall with a score of 45 on a count in. In second place was Bernhardt Steyn and Chris Binneman with 45 points on a count out. John Steynberg and Michael Willemse made the longest drives on the second and eleventh hole respectively. Story and photos: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com Frans Weijters chips the ball onto the green. Last shot onto the green for Dennis Kamstra. Mike Morkel prepares for a shot.